Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

While the wedges cook, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and
thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the onion and stir-fry until soft and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @dried cranberries{30%g}(finely chopped). Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

Put the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a #medium bowl{}, add a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Put the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} and chopped cranberries into a
large #bowl{}, then add half the cooked onion. Pop the remaining onion into a small
bowl and set aside with the pan for later.

Season the sausage meat with salt and pepper, then mix together with your hands.
Roll the mixture into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers (1 per
person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{drizzle}.

Once the oil is hot, add the burgers and fry until browned and cooked through,
~{5-6%minutes} on each side. Carefully turn them every ~{2%minutes} and lower the
heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

Top each burger with the remaining onion, then the grated cheese. Cover with a
#lid{} (or #foil{}), then set aside, off the heat, for ~{3-4%minutes} for the cheese
to melt.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2} and pop them onto a baking tray. When the wedges
are almost cooked, pop the buns on the middle shelf of your oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the bowl of balsamic dressing
and toss to coat.

Pop the buns on your plates and spread the @apple chutney{1} over the bases, then top
with the sausage burgers and bun lids.

Serve with the wedges and rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!